---
// The 1,000,000-note pillar. Big gradient number + three stat cards.
---

<section class="nz-section" id="performance">
  <div class="nz-container">
    <div class="nz-pillar">
      <div class="nz-kicker">The 1,000,000-note test</div>
      <div class="nz-pillar-num">1,000,000</div>
      <h2 class="nz-h2" style="margin-top: 8px;">
        Designed for the user with a million notes.
      </h2>
      <p class="nz-lead" style="max-width: 620px; margin: 16px auto 0;">
        Every feature has to survive that test. If it can't, it doesn't ship.
        That's why search feels instant at any size, why the sidebar never
        stutters, and why the whole app stays out of your way.
      </p>
      <div class="nz-pillar-stats">
        <div class="nz-pillar-stat">
          <div class="num">Instant</div>
          <div class="label">Search, no matter the size</div>
        </div>
        <div class="nz-pillar-stat">
          <div class="num">Already there</div>
          <div class="label">No loading, no waiting</div>
        </div>
        <div class="nz-pillar-stat">
          <div class="num">Featherweight</div>
          <div class="label">Smaller than a single photo</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
